description: The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has been aggressively buying gold for the last few years. Analysis of World Gold Council data shows that the percentage of gold in India’s total foreign exchange reserves has spiked in the last few years.
title: Why is RBI buying gold & how does it help the Indian economy?

description: Posters targeting Rahul Gandhi and INDIA bloc leaders have surfaced in Amethi, accusing them of pro-Pakistan sentiments amid tensions following the Pahalgam attack. The posters feature comments from Farooq Abdullah and Vijay Wadettiwar, labeling Gandhi a terrorism sympathizer.
title: 'INDI's hand with Pakistan': Posters target Rahul Gandhi in Amethi

description: Amid rising tensions, Pakistan's information minister claimed credible intelligence suggests a potential Indian military strike within 24-36 hours, while India accuses Pakistan of violating ceasefire. In the US, an Indian-origin tech entrepreneur killed his family before committing suicide. Meanwhile, Donald Trump defended his China tariffs, and young Vaibhav Suryavanshi became the youngest T20 centurion.
title: Morning news wrap: Pak says India to attack in '24 to 36 hours', & more

description: Formula 1's Oscar Piastri acknowledged cricket's newest sensation, Vaibhav Suryavanshi, after his record-breaking IPL century. At just 14 years old, Vaibhav stunned the world by smashing 101 runs off 38 balls for the Rajasthan Royals. His fearless innings against a world-class bowling attack has marked him as a phenomenon, capturing attention across sports.
title: Oscar Piastri applauds 14-year-old cricket sensation Vaibhav Suryavanshi

description: Virat Kohli's brother, Vikas, has criticized Sanjay Manjrekar on social media following Manjrekar's remarks about Virat's performance in the IPL 2025. Manjrekar suggested Kohli is past his prime, a claim Vikas refuted by highlighting Manjrekar's own ODI strike rate.
title: Virat Kohli's brother slams Sanjay Manjrekar
100 days in office: Trump blows off interviewer 'he never heard of'

description: Harshavardhana Kikkeri, an entrepreneur from Mysuru, allegedly killed his wife, Shwetha, and their son in their Newcastle, Washington home before committing suicide. The couple's younger son was unharmed. Authorities discovered the bodies after responding to a 911 call, with the medical examiner ruling the deaths of Shwetha and her son as homicides and Harshavardhana's as suicide. The motive remains unknown.
title: Bullet on street, blood on window: K'taka techie shoots family dead in US, kills self

description: Chennai Super Kings, struggling with only two wins, face Punjab Kings at Chepauk in a crucial IPL encounter. CSK's batting combinations and powerplay woes persist despite MS Dhoni's return as captain. Punjab Kings, with a stronger position, aim to exploit CSK's weaknesses, leveraging their in-form bowlers against a demoralized Chennai unit in anticipated warm conditions.
title: CSK vs PBKS: Playing XI, MA pitch report, weather in Chennai

description: Vaibhav Suryavanshi's recent century prompted a look back at other Indian teenage cricket prodigies. Sachin Tendulkar's explosive innings against Pakistan at 16, Yuvraj Singh's impactful arrival against Australia, and Irfan Pathan's magical delivery to dismiss Adam Gilchrist are highlighted.
title: From Tendulkar to Yuvraj, when teens conquered our imagination

description: Gold rate prediction: Gold prices have experienced a slight dip despite disappointing US economic data, influenced by hopes of easing US-China trade tensions and President Trump's tariff decisions. Buying gold on Akshaya Tritiya is considered auspicious according to Indian traditions. But what’s the outlook for gold and what factors will drive gold prices in the coming days?
title: Gold rate prediction on Akshaya Tritiya: Where are gold prices headed?

description: In Mangaluru, a man was lynched near Kudupu following allegations of shouting pro-Pakistan slogans during a cricket match. Police have arrested 15 individuals and booked 19 in connection with the incident. Home Minister G Parameshwara has appealed for peace, confirming the death and ongoing investigation.
title: Man lynched for shouting ‘Pakistan zindabad’ during cricket match in Karnataka

description: The Board of Control for Cricket in India is preparing for the England Test series. A pool of players is ready for both the Test team and the India ‘A’ tour. Rohit Sharma is on the shortlist, with selectors deciding on his captaincy. Rajat Patidar and Karun Nair are being considered for the middle order.
title: Rohit Sharma makes BCCI shortlist for Test & ‘A’ tour of England

description: Stock market today: Indian equity benchmark indices, Nifty50 and BSE Sensex, opened in red on Wednesday. While Nifty50 went below 24,300, BSE Sensex was near 80,100. At 9:16 AM, Nifty50 was trading at 24,293.95, down 42 points or 0.17%. BSE Sensex was at 80,133.01, down 155 points or 0.19%.
title: Stock market today: Nifty50 opens below 24,300; BSE Sensex dips over 150 points

description: Vaibhav Suryavanshi, a 14-year-old batting sensation, has captured the attention of cricket legends like Michael Hussey and James Hopes. Hussey likened Vaibhav's explosive batting to Adam Gilchrist's, emphasizing his fearless approach against top bowlers. Hopes highlighted the confidence of 'Gen Z' batters and the strong position of Indian cricket in white-ball formats, noting the exposure young talents receive in India.
title: Vaibhav Suryavanshi reminds me of Adam Gilchrist: Michael Hussey
CEO Kathpalia resigns amid shakeup at IndusInd Bank
China slams US as tensions rise over space observatory project in Chile

description: Pakistan claims to possess credible intelligence indicating an imminent Indian military strike within the next 24 to 36 hours, alleging it's based on fabricated accusations related to the Pahalgam incident. Pakistan vehemently rejects India's self-proclaimed role as judge, jury, and executioner, asserting its own history as a victim of terrorism.
title: 'Credible intel': Pakistan minister claims India planning strike in 24-36 hours

description: Vaibhav Suryavanshi, a prodigious cricket talent from Bihar, overcame age restrictions to shine. Coaches recognized his potential early, fast-tracking him to U-19 cricket where he impressed with aggressive batting. His U-19 Test debut featured a record-breaking century.
title: Homework incomplete, but RR’s boy wonder is rewriting history books
Indian techie kills wife, son, then shoots himself in US home

description: A fire erupted at Hotel Rituraj in Kolkata's Mechhua wholesale fruit market, resulting in one death and multiple injuries. A man died after jumping from a ledge in panic, while another fractured his leg attempting to escape. Firefighters and disaster management teams rescued several individuals, some suffering from smoke inhalation, as concerns arose about others potentially trapped inside.
title: ‘Managed to wriggle out onto a ledge’: How 14 died in Kolkata hotel fire

description: Prince William intends to remove Prince Harry and Meghan Markle's HRH titles once he becomes king, according to media reports. Meghan Markle reportedly continues to use 'Her Royal Highness' in promoting her personal brand, 'As Ever,' despite an alleged promise to the late Queen Elizabeth to stop using the titles after stepping down as senior royals in 2020.
title: Meghan Markle to be stripped off 'HRH' royal title?

description: A video of fans sending water bottles to Hania Aamir has gone viral after India suspends the Indus Water Treaty following the terrorist attack in Pahalgam. Reportedly, Hania has been dropped from Diljit Dosanjh's 'Sardaarji 3' now.
title: Pak actor Hania Aamir gets water bottles from Indians after Indus Treaty suspension

description: Stock market recommendations: Anand Rathi Shares and Stock Brokers' DVP Mehul Kothari recommends buying Inox Wind, Symphony, and Jyoti CNC. Inox Wind, exhibiting strength above its 200 DEMA, is a buy in the ₹170-₹173 range, targeting ₹190. Symphony, recovering from a recent decline, is poised to retest its moving averages, with a target of ₹1260.
title: Top stocks to buy today: Stock recommendations for today

description: US President Donald Trump defended his trade policies, asserting China would likely bear the tariff costs. In an ABC News interview, Trump dismissed concerns about price increases, stating China was "ripping us off." He doubled down on China tariffs, saying 'They deserve it.
title: Trump defends China tariffs, says 'they deserve it'

description: Following their IPL match, Delhi Capitals' Kuldeep Yadav playfully slapped KKR's Rinku Singh, both representing Uttar Pradesh, in a friendly exchange. KKR defeated DC by 14 runs, boosting their playoff hopes. KKR's innings was propelled by Angkrish Raghuvanshi (44) and Rinku Singh (36), while Sunil Narine's 3/29 restricted DC to 190/9 despite contributions from Faf du Plessis and Axar Patel.
title: WATCH: Kuldeep Yadav caught slapping Rinku Singh on camera

description: As Akshaya Tritiya approaches, a new study suggests the gold in your jewelry and smartphones may originate from magnetar explosions billions of years ago. NASA data indicates that powerful flares from magnetars could account for up to 10% of heavy elements, including gold.
title: Where does gold come from? Nasa has the answer
Tigress survives years with snare knotted around stomach, raises healthy cubs

description: At least seven people were killed and several injured when a wall collapsed at the Sri Varaha Lakshmi Narasimha Swamy Temple in Simhachalam, Andhra Pradesh, early Wednesday morning. The incident, triggered by heavy rain and strong winds around 2.30am, occurred just before the temple's first darshan on Akshaya Tritiya. Rescue efforts by NDRF and state teams are ongoing. Authorities have assured a thorough investigation and compensation for victims.
title: 7 killed in wall collapse at temple in Andhra Pradesh's Simhachalam

description: Donald Trump's remarks about Taylor Swift create controversy before the Kansas City Chiefs' White House visit. The Chiefs are visiting to celebrate their Super Bowl victory. Trump previously praised Kelce but now mocks Swift. This adds tension to the event. It raises questions about Kelce's attendance. The situation complicates what should be a celebration of the team's achievement.
title: Trump’s latest jab at Swift could derail Kansas City Chiefs’ White House visit
14 killed as fire rips through hotel in Kolkata, rescue ops under way

description: Sunny Deol's 'Jaat,' following the blockbuster 'Gadar 2,' has faced a slowdown at the box office. While it initially maintained a steady pace, new releases have begun to overshadow its performance. Despite a weekend surge, the film experienced a significant drop on its third Monday, struggling to reach the one crore mark. 'Jaat' has earned ₹86.30 Cr in total.
title: 'Jaat' box office day 20: Sunny Deol starrer inches towards Rs 90cr

description: An Air India Express flight from Pune to Jaipur faced a setback. A passenger fell ill due to a faulty air conditioning system. The flight had to return to the bay before takeoff. The airline provided medical assistance to the affected passenger. Passengers were offered refunds or rescheduling options. Air India Express regretted the inconvenience caused to its passengers.
title: Woman flyer falls ill after AC failure on Pune-Jaipur Air India Express flight

description: In Faridabad, Amit Bhadana, a former banker, delivers milk in his Audi A3 cabriolet. He covers 60-70km daily, serving around 120 litres to households. Amit switched from his Harley Davidson due to the summer heat. His family runs a dairy farm with cows and buffaloes. Despite fuel costs, he enjoys delivering milk in style.
title: Banker-turned-milkman now delivers milk in Rs 50 lakh Audi across Faridabad

description: Following reports of Amazon planning to display tariff costs, President Trump reportedly contacted Jeff Bezos, expressing concerns about the potential impact on consumer perception of his trade policies. Subsequently, Amazon downplayed the report and scrapped the plan entirely.
title: Amazon founder Jeff Bezos gets call from very angry Donald Trump

description: Pakistan claims to have shot down an Indian quadcopter, alleging airspace violation amid escalating tensions and cross-border firing. This incident follows the Pahalgam attack, further straining relations as both nations engage in retaliatory measures, including trade suspensions and military posturing. With heightened rhetoric and media fueling the conflict, the region teeters on the brink of a broader confrontation.
title: Pakistan claims it downed Indian drone, tensions escalate along LoC
India packs fizz for Coke amid weak global markets
Patent regime: US retains India on 'priority watch list'

description: President Trump indicated that tariff discussions with India are progressing positively, raising hopes for a potential agreement. Both nations are actively pursuing "early mutual wins" to finalize key aspects of the bilateral trade agreement by the Fall of 2025. Discussions have already commenced, with further in-person sectoral engagements planned for late May to achieve tangible outcomes before the deadline.
title: Tariff talks with India going great, think we'll have a deal, says Trump
Acquitted 10yrs ago, ‘Pak man’ remains in jail as Islamabad says not our citizen
